HEADWORD: Boodle
<hw>Boo"dle</hw> <pr>(b⟦oomac⟧"d`l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Origin
uncertain.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The whole collection or lot;
caboodle.</def> <mark>[Low, U. S.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bartlett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Money given in payment for votes or political
influence; bribe money; swag.</def> <mark>[Polit. slang, U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bogey</ent>⟦br⟧
